description: Special financing available—potential 5% mortgage rate! Contact your agent for details. Welcome to high-rise living with unbeatable access to everything Atlanta has to offer! This beautifully appointed 1-bedroom, 1-bath condo on the 18th floor offers nearly 1,000 square feet of thoughtfully designed space, combining comfort, convenience, and city sophistication. Bonus: it comes with a valuable storage unit, and the unit itself offers even more built-in storage than you’d expect. Soaked in natural light thanks to large windows, the open layout highlights hardwood floors, a modern kitchen with maple cabinetry, granite countertops, stainless steel Bosch appliances, a SubZero fridge, and a gas range—a rare luxury in condo living. Smart features abound, including a Nest thermostat, smart lock entry, dimmer lights throughout, and a timed fan in the bathroom. Unwind with skyline and Piedmont Park views from your oversized private patio—perfect for morning coffee or evening wine. The spacious bedroom is a peaceful retreat with custom blackout drapes, a generous walk-in closet, and direct access to a spa-like bath with a soaking tub and separate shower. There’s also an in-unit washer and dryer for everyday ease. Life at The Luxe is luxury redefined: this boutique, fob-access-only building features just 116 homes and is professionally managed with 24-hour concierge, on-site management, building maintenance, and housekeeping. Enjoy amenities like a saltwater pool, grills, gym, steam room, lockers, massage room, clubhouse with kitchen, conference room, guest suite, secure parking, monthly community events, pet walk and dog park.  The building is also well insulated and incredibly quiet—perfect for city living. Rental permits are available, and the HVAC and water heater are both newer.  With Piedmont Park right outside your door, and  Whole Foods, restaurants, shops, and cultural hotspots all within blocks, this is your chance to own a piece of Atlanta’s vibrant Midtown scene.
